                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.612 Oranges/Spain/—: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moore</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-12-09T23:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 9, 1925—11 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 9—8:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>76. Has the Department of Agriculture placed an embargo on Spanish oranges? An
                    immediate answer is vital to every American business interest in Spain.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
